###### Installation notes for TSRchitect
#Before you begin using TSRchitect, you will need to install its R packages dependencies, most of which are available in Bioconductor.
#Installation of the required packages can be done in the following manner from your R console:
source("https://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R")
biocLite(c(GenomeInfoDb, GenomicAlignments, GenomicRanges, Rsamtools, BiocParallel))

#installing TSRchitect from source
## from a linux/unix command line:
>$ git clone https://github.com/BrendelGroup/TSRchitect
>$ R CMD INSTALL TSRchitect

# to make sure it loads correctly on your system, do the following from an R console
>$ R --vanilla #launching R
> library(TSRchitect) #loading TSRchitect
